<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  Representative sample of the Portuguese Trusted List (ETSI TS 119 612), authored for
  offline tests of `chancela-tsl`. It mirrors the real structure published by the Gabinete
  Nacional de Seguranca (GNS) but the certificates are ephemeral self-signed fixtures, NOT
  real QTSP CAs. See crates/chancela-tsl/TESTING.md.

  Coverage:
    - TSP "MULTICERT ..."  -> CA/QC, GRANTED, ForeSignatures  => qualified for e-sig.
      (also carries a ServiceHistory withdrawn instance the parser MUST ignore.)
    - TSP "DigitalSign ..." -> CA/QC, WITHDRAWN                => present but not qualified.
    - TSP "EGIA ..."        -> CA/QC, GRANTED, ForeSeals only  => present but not for e-sig.
    - TSP "Cartorio Notarial Timestamping" -> TSA/QTST, GRANTED => not a CA/QC (ignored for e-sig).
      Also carries an accent-heavy alias, a supply point, and a revoked TSA/TST edge record
      with a malformed status date and no service name.
-->
